result.execSummary:
The defendant Jacy M. Walters was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC (2nd+ Offense), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Jacy M. Walters in court with attorney Justin D. Wolff.  Kristi S. Tlusty appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Agreement placed on the record.  DE entered a plea of no contest to Ct. 1.  Plea colloquy.  Court found plea given freely, voluntarily, and intelligenlty; accepted plea; found DE guilty and ordered entry of JOC.  Pursuant to the agreement all remaining charges are dismissed and read in as well as citation 14FO120 is dismissed outright on state's motion.  Brief comments by Mr. Wolff.    Court withheld sentence and placed De on probation for three years with the following conditions:  5 days county jail with Huber, with agent to decide when or how jail time is served, but no later than 02/28/2015; $100 fine plus court costs; DNA sample and pay surcharge; payment of $55.60 SOP fees; AODA and follow through with treatment; and other counseling as deemed appropriate by agent.
